author: @reubenadams7054
text: *try clause* -- Runs until it finishes or an exception is raised. *except clauses* -- These are checked (and then run if the exception matches) in order if and only if an exception was raised, either until it's caught or we run out of except clauses. *else clause* -- Runs if and only if the try clause did not raise any exceptions. *finally clause* -- Always runs, even if there were exceptions and even if they weren't caught.  *code after try/except block* -- Runs if and only if no exception was raised, or one was raised but was caught.
